{{champion:15}} 

Sivir loves black cleaver. With her q and w, she very quickly applies 5 stacks to the entire enemy team. The added cdr will make her able to q and w more frequently.

{{item:3071}} {{item:3031}} {{item:3508}} {{item:3172}} {{item:3072}} {{item:3035}}

Ad fighters for the most part. Vi, Jarvan, Lee Sin, Darius etc. Any fighter that starts the game with one offensive item and then ends up going full tank for the most part after that. It will be situational for most of these champs, but it let's them grab another offensive item without feeling like they can't stay relevant in teamfights. It gives a decent amount of Health so it is going to be an optional second offensive item for those fighters who want a bruiser set up that lets them fight tanks (they would sacrifice a defensive item for this or they would use it as their main offensive item). Also, more offensive bruisers such as Urgot (Pantheon also) will love this item. It gives him more sticking power to hit his acid hunters and more armor shred to take out front lines. (Bonus for Urgot = extra CDR). 

An example of a champion build that this item will be a part of: 

{{champion:59}} : {{item:3707}}(jung){{item:3071}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3190}} {{item:3075}} 


or for a laner {{champion:122}} : {{item:3071}} {{item:3068}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3102}} {{item:3083}} 

As a side note: I don't really play either of these champions.... I'm kinda guestimating their builds based on what I've seen. I do know that Darius loves the Rage passive (plus he has passive armor pen), and Jarvan benefits a lot from the armor shred. These are just example builds and are not optimal for all situations. For example, if Darius was facing a magic damage opponent, Hexdrinker would be a great starting item. Phage into CLeaver would still be an option later. Hope you get an idea of what the item was made for. It's to help fighters deal with tanks in the late game when tanks have a lot or armor. Good luck.
